An illicit hooley in the heart of Temple Bar, with a line-up of shameless jazzy grooves and lascivious foreign rhythms, defying the decency of our 1935 Public Dancehalls Act 
www.downwithjazz.ie    
Summer festival hijinks kick off with Down With Jazz festival this June Bank Holiday weekend (30/31 May) in the annual city-centre celebration of musical rebellion, with jazz, experimental and world music acts over 2 nights in Meeting House Square. 
“The festival with a sense of humour” (The Irish Times) harks back to 1930s Ireland when jazz and ‘foreign’ music was seen by the Catholic Church as a filthy force of corruption, and a repressive ‘anti-jazz’ campaign pushed to ban jazz from the dance halls and airwaves of Ireland. Today’s Down With Jazz festival links audiences with 21st century Ireland’s vibrant and diverse music scene through the tongue-in-cheek prism of this notorious period of social history. 
2015 sees the 80th anniversary of the controversial, and still legit Dancehalls Act (1935). The act was devised as a means of control and repression of ‘immoral’ jazz dances, yet the result was the death of the rural Irish tradition of ‘dancing at the crossroads’ which became illegal, also making ‘house dances’ and the ‘hooley in the kitchen’ punishable with a hefty fine. Parish halls were erected with dancing strictly patrolled by members of the clergy and taxes on entry went direct to the government. The Dancehalls Act has been widely cited by historians to be a pivotal factor in the decline of Irish traditional music performance in Ireland. 
Fast forward 80 years and Down With Jazz presents top level Irish jazz in the form of legendary guitarist Louis Stewart with his quintet, as well as Hugh Buckley’s Isotope, bringing JJ’s Smyth’s jazz to Temple Bar. Contemporary piano trio The CEO Experiment join forces with acclaimed saxophonist and producer Michael Buckley. Seventeen-piece Dublin City Jazz Orchestra will be bustin’ it out big-band style, and audiences can funk it up with Joe O Callaghan’s jazz-fusion trio Electric Freeplay 
Fully live and improvised hip-hop collective Mixtapes From the Underground make a welcome return with their "scorching collision of Jazz and Hip Hop” (The Irish Times). High level rhythms from West African by renowned djembe and n’goni player Sidiki Dembélé, performing in Ireland for the very first time with members of Dublin’s Manden Express. And an exciting mix of Irish traditional dance tunes and 90’s hip-hop beats from Jiggy, led by percussionist Robbie Harris.  
Look forward to a a trip through Zappa-esque jazz and funk grooves with six piece act Tongue Bundle, plus top level prog-rock and contemporary jazz from instrumental quartet Leo Drezden. 
Come down to the square for a hooley and enjoy some of the finest jazz and experimental music acts under the canopies in Temple Bar. 
www.downwithjazz.ie 
  
#downwithjazz2015

//a Tech Carnival 
 Bailey Allen Hall, NUI Galway 23.9.15  
What is Synapse?  
Synapse //a Tech Carnival, is a student organised, one day interactive technology showcase of top companies in the University.  Our goal is to put context to the knowledge given to us by our lecturers, discover new technologies and give a more definitive, personal and creative direction to our career path. We aim to tear down the norms, and have a day that is about the technology.  
Why create Synapse?  
We wanted to create an event in order to provide a platform for students to integrate themselves with industry professionals at a more technical level and prepare themselves for a life in tech.  
What do we hope to achieve?  
By running this event, it is our greatest ambition that all students who attend will grasp real time insights into working for tech’s biggest players.  
Our 2014 event was a massive success - we did good !  
On the day we had over 1,200 students in attendance interactIng with over 30 of the tech industry’s top firms, including Microsoft, HP, Avaya to name but a few. They showcased their latest cutting edge technology - everything from 3d printers, revolutionary gaming platforms and groundbreaking sim technology.  
Students and companies had unique opportunities throughout the day to network with each other. Companies got to meet the top talent of students and the students get face to face with the industry’s finest - a winning combination ! 
Synapse ‘15 is shaping up to be even bigger.  
We are not standing still! With this year’s event we are pushing the boundaries, capitalising on the success of 2014 and promising to make Synapse ’15 a day to remember. We are close to securing even more of the biggest tech companies out there for our next event.  
After all this is Synapse //a Tech Carnival - bringing the biggest names in tech to galway ;-)  If you would like your company to be at the biggest tech event in the country, outside of Dublin, then get in touch and we will make it happen.  
Have an awesome day ! 
 - Team Synapse  
www.SynapseGalway.com

The annual Shawbrook Forest Festival takes place on the last weekend of May. A family friendly boutique festival of dance and music. Shawbrook is a traditional 18th century Irish farm-house with bespoke dance studios, set amidst a magical forest of oak, ash and beech trees. The day kicks off with solo dance performances from talented young dancers. There will be a communal picnic in the forest with a range of acts on the open-stage to entertain you. Local band ARROW IN THE SKY are this year's music headline act. Later in the evening, West End star Ruth Berkeley will host a cabaret night in the theatre studio.  
There is a wonderful atmosphere at the Forest Festival and people have come back year after year to enjoy high quality dance and music in a relaxed environment. Previous perfoermes include Liam O'Maonlaoi, Gemma Hayes and Preachers Son. This festival is perfect for families. There is secure on-site parking available, so no long trek to the performances. Shawbrook is only 1 hour 20 mins from Dublin. 
Camping is available. Please email us in advance to secure a place.  
Shawbrook has accommodation avaiable through Air BnB. 
  
FAQs 
  
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event? 
On site parking is available. (No long trek to the stage!) 
  
What can/can't I bring to the event? 
Please bring your own food and drink and be considerate not to leave any rubbish behind.  There are no on-site food stalls. 
  
Where can I contact the organizer with any questions? 
If you have further queries, please email shawbrook@gmail.com

This June Bank Holiday weekend, North Wall Quay will once again play host to the Dublin Port Riverfest. There will be a wide array of activities throughout the duration of the festival, including the arrival of ten tall ships and schooners which will berth at North Wall Quay for the weekend. 
As well as the ships there will be amusements, tug boat dancing, kayaking and more, so there is something for all the family to enjoy! This year the festival is pirate themed, so have fun dressing up and there will be prizes for the best fancy dress costumes! 
Entry into this event is FREE. 
FAQs 
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event? 
No, this is an event for all the family. 
  
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event? 
Travelling to Dublin Port Riverfest couldn’t be easier. We are situated in the heart of Dublin’s docklands which is well served by public transport. Bus, Rail and DART services all leave you within a few minutes walk to North Wall Quay and the Luas Red Line leaves you right at  The Festival’s doorstep. 
  
The best way to get to Dublin Port Riverfest is by using the festival’s transport partner LUAS. The LUAS RED LINE leaves you at the Festival’s doorstep, just stroll to the Liffey quayside in less than 2 minutes and you’re there! 
DART 
DART  networks provide excellent service from many different parts of Dublin. In most cases parking is available at the various stations along the route. 
Dublin Bus 
Dublin Bus offers a high frequency, accessible and easy to use service from all over Dublin to within a 20 minute walk of the Venue. 
The 151 route operates every 10 minutes during rush hour and will leave you on Castleforbes Rd, the closest stop to the Venue, only 2 minutes walk away. The last bus departs Castleforbes Road at 23.15pm Mon – Sat.  
Road Routes 
If you plan on driving to the festival, please note that traffic restrictions are in place on North Wall Quay and on East Wall Road. 
Where can I contact the organiser with any questions? 
Email: info@idea.ie

description.text:
At the Bhakti Fest of Hope 2015 a fanciful array of whimsical treasures awaits you to delight & behold by the river side in the 'Fairy Garden at Beirnes of Battle Bridge' on the banks of Leitrim & Roscommon border. 
Come out & play with us in the pretty garden! There'll be fire dancers, acrobats, clowns, face painting, kids yoga, marquee, tipis, puppet making workshop, hoop artists, Kirtan, drumming, craft & fancy stalls, vegan & vegetarian food, Mehndi, tribal dance, art & craft workshops, yoga classes, camping, chill out zone, kids DJ, sound bath, inspirational speaker, & a twinkling evening concert all under the star lit sky! 
All of the money raised over the weekend will be going directly to the Hope Foundation who help vulnerable children living on the streets & slums of Calcutta in India by feeding, clothing, giving medical assistance, education, and providing shelter from the predators & dangers that surround them every day. 
Namaste & go raibh maith agat a milliún! 
  
FAQs 
  
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event? 
Please bring you ID with you. Under 16 must be accompanied by an adult. 
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event? 
There will be allocared parking spaces in Leitrim Village which is a 10 minute walk to the event. 
We will also have a 'set down' area for cars to drop off people / camping gear 
  
What can/can't I bring to the event? 
No illegal drugs on the premises.  
No dogs, unless guide dogs. 
Bring a cushion / seat  
  
Where can I contact the organiser with any questions? 
contact: 086 152 68 33 
  
Is my registration/ticket transferrable? 
Yes 
  
Can I update my registration information? 
Yes 
  
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event? 
Yes 
  
What is the refund policy? 
No refunds, sorry! This is your donation to the Hope Foundation  
  
The name on the registration/ticket doesn't match the attendee. Is that okay? 
No, you need to go online & change your details  or contact 086 152 68 33 
  
where do I pay for camping?  
the camp gate will open from 4pm on Fri 12th June & is on a 1st come, 1st served basis.  
€10 per pitch at the gate entrance for Fri & Sat night.  
  
 What are the camp regulations? 
please respect that this is a family event with children & all music must be off by 12am midnight. Some people will be practicing early morning meditation, therefore please no shouting or yoddeling in the morning between 7am - 10am :-)

__________________________________________________________________________________
Located on a 300 year old family farm in the Burren Mountains of Ireland, Hazel Mountain Chocolate is a bean to bar chocolate factory, founded in 2014 by John & Kasha Connolly.
Hazel Mountian Chocolate makes craft chocolate from the bean to the bar. Starting with Cacao beans sourced from all around the world through direct trade.  Then roast, crack, winnow, stonegrind and finally finish and pack our chocolate, all under the one roof here in the Burren on Ireland's Wild Atlantic Way.
Hazel Mountain Chocolate hold events, such as guided tours of our bean to bar shed and tasting room, monthly evening dinners in our farm to fork cafe & private parties.

description.text:
The ShakeFest 10th Year Anniversary Celebrations will be our best and biggest yet, and take place once more this summer (May 30th - 31st) at Charleville Castle. This is a community run holistic fair day for families, international dance enthusiasts and anyone active! 
ShakeFest is a “Shake-It-Up” annual family day participative art event to celebrate imagination, action, creativity, and the colourful possibilities through art expression, exchange, learning, performance and fun! 
  
ShakeFest is an inclusive Multi-Ethnic exotic food event focusing on multicultural workshops, creative play and performance events from local, national and international groups; Performers and Educators who bring their own following backed by advertising, social-media and awareness events. 
This event recognises the value in a great family day out - we have many free interactive activites and workshops for families, children and all ages. 
  
Each year we also introduce a new International Master Artist, Instructor and Performer to Ireland - this year it is Tribal Dance Troupe RUSTIQUA from Slovakia!   
Shakefest wil have special 10 Year Anniversary Celebration treats like amazing animation projections on Charleville Castle by Bunny & the Beardman and free gifts at the gate! 
  
Shakefest also holds an annual eclectic Fire Performance Show with Fire Bellydancers, Hula Hoopers and Circus groups and encourages on-site overnight camping under the stars on the Charleville Castle grounds, in which revellers should expect to be asked to join drumming at campfires and friendly banter. 
  
Introductory workshops are only €5 and are drop in, most children's workshops are free, and specialty dance workshops for dancers are €12 which require booking in advance. 
  
If you have any questions about Shakefest or advance workshop bookings, please check us out at www.shakefest.net and go to 'Contact'.  Please print out your proof of purchase once ticket has been purchased on Eventbrite and show at the gate for entry.

description.text:
Different types of dance and culture are easily available in larger communities and cities in Ireland, and in bringing such a variety ‘Shake – A Celebration of Dance’ helps link such creativity together at Charleville Castle, Tullamore.
Shake consists of an educational series of dance workshops starting from 12pm Saturday, May 30th and Sunday, May 31st along with an evening of cultural performances starting at 8pm on Saturday, May 30th. It is purposely orchestrated with a multicultural and international theme; in line with a new Ireland, that leads to an evening of a multicultural dance of excellence.
Shake over the past years has grown from a day of Energy, Movement and Dance to a unique week-end of multicultural and international relaxation and holistic living – Come for the week-end – stay locally or camp around the castle – but also, if you prefer, just pop-in for your preferred course – this is a special time-out for everyone – every age – every taste – a community switching-on!
ALL of Shakefest’s proceeds go to The Charleville Castle Restoration Fund which aids in sustaining important intercultural volunteer training programmes, the 200 year old Neo-Gothic structure itself, and future fundraisers. This particular event sponsors operation RAISE THE ROOF – in which all proceeds will go towards the construction of a new roof on the castle chapel. Charleville Castle is an Independent Arts and Culture Center of the Irish Midlands and encourages arts, culture and dance mediums of all kinds.

description.text:
The Secret Garden Music Festival is a family oriented music event focussing on established and popular headline acts. We also create a space where new Irish musical artists get the opportunity to showcase their talent. We cater for a wide audience with something for everyone.  
  
On top of the music events the Secret Garden Music festival is also a space that exhibits works of art and sculpture from local artists and artistic volunteers. This sits side by side with our craft fair selling many unusual hand made and one of a kind items. Being a family oriented event, we have a number of games and spaces created for children, filled with unique games and fun filled entertainment. Including face painting and bouncy castle.  
  
There will be a large number of food stalls at the event with a variety of cuisines from around the world similar to an ethnic food fare or artisan market with food to cater for every palette. This festival is the first of its kind to be hosted in Wicklow Town and highlights the town and surrounding area as wonderful place to visit and will help to promote tourism and passing trade during the festival.

BloomFringe Festival 2015 -  Green Gorgeous & Guerrilla

BloomFringe Festival is the younger, edgier and rather irreverent cousin of Bloom In the Phoenix Park. Her summer events cluster takes place between May 30th and the June Bank Holiday Monday in Dublin at various city centre locations supported by Dublin City council. It is fuelled by grassroots support, social enterprise, inspired collaborations and where possible, composed mainly of free events - including open days, talks, retail trails, secret dublin tours, workshops, art installations and foodie pop-up moments. 
BloomFringe doesn't do de rigeuer garden displays, she will be doing avant gardens instead. The sort of garden festival that shuns the exurbs, preferring to play amongst inner city streets whilst highlighting Dublin’s potential as a Blath Cliath - backed by Dublin city Council with media support by LeCool Dublin. 
This not-for-profit fringe festival is motivated by themes such as creativity, community, healthy living and sustainable biodiversity. BloomFringe spotlights vibrant gardening communities with a mission to grow the grass in grassroots. There will be art installations at Dublin’s neglected alleyways, as creative fringesters turn them into lanes that are loved. Unafraid of concrete, BloomFringe embraces the challenge to reintroduce nature. She is an urban interventionist guerrilla gardener sporting fatigues and seed bombs, ready to put the jungle back in urban jungle. Bloomfringe loves to sow and reap ideas, growing potential and harvesting the love and labour by communities and organisations that have set about improving Dublin life for all to enjoy. See Dublin through her instagram eyes @bloomfringe. 
Where ideas don’t go to seed, where inspiration grows, wherever you find Bloomfringe.

On May 30th, the first annual Castlebar Artisan Food and Music Festival will be held in The Military Barracks, in Castlebar town. The family friendly event will run for one day and will provide entertainment to people of all ages. 

For the food lovers of the west of Ireland, the event will host up to 50 local artisan food, drink and craft stalls. The stalls will be presenting an array of different local produce. Everything from specialty jams and breads, to sausages and beer! As well as showing off their goods, some of these local producers will be providing demonstrations throughout the day that will show how to best prepare and serve their produce, and maybe some secrets to their recipes.Two Outdoor Stages will be the centerpiece of the event, with live music and live cooking demonstrations all shown on the big screen and a separate Acoustic stage showcasing the best in local talent, this event is not to be missed.
  
A selection of handpicked chefs from around the region will take to the main demonstration stage. These chefs will be providing live cooking demonstrations and will show the audience how to prepare some of their signature dishes, from start to finish. These include Barry Ralph – Flogas Mayo Masterchef Winner and head chef of the Bay Leaf Restaurant. Chef, restaurateur and author, JP McMahon – Culinary director of the EatGalway Restaurant, network leader for the global Cook it Raw project and an ambassador for Spanish food in Ireland to name a few. 
Despite all of the food related entertainment on offer, the festival is as much about good music as it is about good food. The live music stage will play host to some of the best Irish Artists of 2015 including Tucan, The Young Folk, and local artists The New Social. The festival will conclude with a live performance by the no.1 selling artist, Damien Dempsey. The Dubliner will be bringing his full band to blow the Mayo food lovers away with his powerful folk ballads. 
To top it all off, the Castlebar Artisan Food and Music Festival will be providing a Children’s play area, which will provide endless amounts of fun the little ones including bouncy castles, face painting, games etc. and best of all… it’s FREE! (Children must be supervised by a guardian at all times) 
  

 Contact us at artisancastlebar@gmail.com 
  
Tickets are NOW ON SALE from the following outlets Downtown Records and entertainment.ie Link http://e1.ie/33vu Price: Adult: €25 + booking fee Young adult and OAP: €12.50 + booking fee Kids under 12: Free 
  

When purchasing an adult ticket if you are bringing kids under 12 make sure to get one ticket for each kid under 12. MAX 2 kids per adult. All under 18's MUST be accompanied by an appropriate adult.

The Connemara Walking Festival is set in Ireland's breathtaking Connemara region - a Hill Walker's haven. Be part of this social gathering of hill walking enthusiasts and explore the wild landscape of the west. Climb some of Galway's highest mountain ranges such as the Twelve Bens or set out on a low level cultural tour of the area around Doolough and Killary Harbour. Take some snapshots of Connemara's magical rugged terrain and discover the area with local mountain leaders and cultural tour guides.  
  
The festivities take place at Delphi Adventure Resort & Spa, a 4* Hotel with onsite hostel accommodation. Nestled amongst the scenic splendours of Ireland's Wild Atlantic Way, the resort is the perfect location for exploring Connemara's unique offering.  
  
The festival kicks off with an opening ceremony featuring a diverse range of guest speakers, locally sourced food prepared by our award-winning chef, traditional Irish music and dancing, and continues throughout the weekend with professionally guided hill walks through some of Connemara's most awe-inspiring mountain landscapes. A closing ceremony takes place on the Sunday evening to share experiences and to make life long memories with new friends and old. With walks to suit all fitness levels (Low, Moderate & High), there is something for everyone - come and join us for the festivities! 
  
Ticket types:   - 1 & 2 Day Passes (walk only) - Weekend Passes (inlcluding all evening activities and most meals) - All-Inclusive Weekend Pass (walks, evening activities, most meals and accommodation) Available here 
More information about the event here: www.delphi.ie

description.text: Relay for Life Dun Laoghaire Rathdown is a 24 hour event which takes place in Blackrock Park. The Relay For Life events rai...se vital funds to support the Work of the Irish Cancer Society. At the heart of each Relay For Life event, teams of friends, neighbours, families and colleagues come together in groups and commit to keeping participants walking around a track or path for 24 hours. Hundreds of other activities take place throughout the 24 hours to create a wonderfully festive atmosphere. The event starts with a cancer survivor's lap of honour.  Cancer can leave a lot of pain and heartache in its wake. But it can also inspire people to come together and do some wonderful things. Relay For Life events are organised entirely by communities so that those lost to cancer will never be forgotten, that those who face cancer will be supported, and in the hope that one day cancer will be eliminated. With your help, we hope to bring Relay For Life to every town and city in Ireland. The Relay brings the whole community together to Celebrate the lives of cancer Survivors, to Remember those whom we have lost to the disease and to Fight Back by increasing our knowledge of cancer and by raising money to fund vital research and services of The Irish Cancer Society. At RELAY FOR LIFE, teams & families, colleagues or friends commit to having at least one member of their team walking around the track at all times. While they are doing that, a festival of fun & entertainment takes place which unites everybody in the fight against cancer. The money raised by RELAY enables the Irish Cancer Society to continue its life saving work.

Relay for Life Dun Laoghaire Rathdown is a 24 hour event which takes place in Blackrock Park. The Relay For Life events rai...se vital funds to support the Work of the Irish Cancer Society. At the heart of each Relay For Life event, teams of friends, neighbours, families and colleagues come together in groups and commit to keeping participants walking around a track or path for 24 hours. Hundreds of other activities take place throughout the 24 hours to create a wonderfully festive atmosphere. The event starts with a cancer survivor's lap of honour.
Cancer can leave a lot of pain and heartache in its wake. But it can also inspire people to come together and do some wonderful things. Relay For Life events are organised entirely by communities so that those lost to cancer will never be forgotten, that those who face cancer will be supported, and in the hope that one day cancer will be eliminated. With your help, we hope to bring Relay For Life to every town and city in Ireland. The Relay brings the whole community together to Celebrate the lives of cancer Survivors, to Remember those whom we have lost to the disease and to Fight Back by increasing our knowledge of cancer and by raising money to fund vital research and services of The Irish Cancer Society. At RELAY FOR LIFE, teams & families, colleagues or friends commit to having at least one member of their team walking around the track at all times. While they are doing that, a festival of fun & entertainment takes place which unites everybody in the fight against cancer. The money raised by RELAY enables the Irish Cancer Society to continue its life saving work.

July 25th & 26th 2015 
  
Organised by An Ríocht Athletic Club and Castleisland Rugby Club the two day event will bring an unprecedented festival atmosphere to the town. On Saturday, hundreds will take on the obstacles as they go out in their respective waves. Saturday evening will see the Galway band ‘Amazing Apples’ take to the stage in the marquee followed by a dj to take the crowd into the early hours. 
  
This years event sees a second day scheduled with a jam packed Sunday. Hercoileán- The Expo will be an opportunity for local businesses to showcase their products or services, with lots on display for young and old it fits the bill as the perfect family day out. The expo will be followed by an ‘easy Sunday session’ with more live music to bring a busy weekend in the island to a close.  
  
Hercoileán, the island warrior challenge: 
Hercoileán is a military style challenge course, 7.5km in distance. Think military bootcamp meets childhood fantasy of taking on the world and getting pretty messed up doing so. The event was hugely successful in its inaugural running last year and we’ve decided that we are going bigger and better for 2015.  
  
Competitors will be faced with a variety of obstacles as they make their way around the course. Obstacles will test the body and mind but while doing so are sure to make you laugh out loud and leave you with a feel good factor!! 
  
Tackle Together: Gather a group and we’ll make sure you all go off in the same wave. Friends/teammates/work colleagues are sure to help you on your way round, you’ll feel less wet, less mucky, much stronger, and way faster!* (*Disclaimer: this is completely dependent on the profile of teammates involved) This year there will also be reduced rate U.18 waves, so grab your classmates and take on the obstacles together. 
  
Hugely positive responses came in after last years event with ‘the craic’ that was had on the course being the most discussed topic. 
  
Rates: 
  
Early Early Bird- Enter before 31st May 2015: €30 (includes after party ticket) 
Early Bird- Enter before 19th July: €35 (includes after party ticket) 
Sun 19th-Fri 24th July 2015: €40 (includes after party ticket) 
  
Hercoileán: The After Party 
Once completed, it’s the perfect excuse to get together for a celebration of your athleticism, toughness and heroism on the day….or simply a time to revel in your combined ability to look ridiculous whilst overcoming obstacles. Galway band, Amazing Apples will take to the stage on Saturday night to help you celebrate.  
Alternatively, you can join the after party celebration without having taken on the challenge earlier in the day. Tickets for the party will be available from reception and online at www.riocht.ie 
  
About The Band: 
'Amazing Apples’ are a 5 piece multi instrumentalist Indie/Folk band from Galway. In March 2014 they released their second single, 'Slipping By', which peaked at no. 1 on the iTunes downloads charts, and stayed in the Official Irish Charts for 2 weeks. Also in 2014 they headlined the Bier Hall Stage at Indiependence Festival, and played their first UK festival at Hamswell. This band were just last week shortlisted by Hot Press Magazine to appear on the cover as part of their Big Break Competition. 
  
Hercoileán The Expo & Car Boot Sale: 
  
An opportunity for local business to showcase their products or services and with a range of attractions will be a fantastic family day out. Indoor and Outdoor stalls will be available, to book or for more info email info@riocht.ie or contact 087 6870581. 
  
  
Exciting times ahead!!

description.text:
Ireland's traveling marionette (string puppet) theatre, Moon & Sixpence, present a cheeky version of “Red Riding Hood” featuring the classic fairy-tale characters and a talking dustbin, who encourages children to pick up litter. 
This string puppet production includes a moral in the tale, showing the importance of patience and friendship. The production, lasting fifty minutes, is performed live with music and sound effects and draws plenty of audience participation, as much from adults as from children. 
Temple Gate Hotel, Ennis, Co. Clare 
Friday 3rd of July 2015 
Two Shows: 4pm & 6pm (duration 50min.)
